      • buildArrayOfFile

        public static ArrayOfFile buildArrayOfFile(java.lang.String storageBucketId,
                                           java.lang.String path,
                                           java.lang.String virtualPath,
                                           java.lang.String[] filenames)
        Builds an array of Files that have the same storageBucketId from an array of file names (or relative paths) that are mapped from path on the server to virtualPath in the execution environment. This is especially useful for multiple files in the same directory. Furthermore, it can save much boiler even if used with path and/or virtualPath set to "" and a list of paths as filenames.
        Parameters:
        storageBucketId - the ID of the storage bucket.
        path - the base path of the files in the server.
        virtualPath - the base path of the files in the execution environment.
        filenames - the names (or relative paths) of the files.
        Returns:
        the generated ArrayOfFile.
